  "prompt": "How did Oliver Sykes damaged his voice exactly?",
  "response": "Oliver Sykes, the lead vocalist of the band Bring Me the Horizon, experienced significant damage to his voice primarily due to the intense vocal style he employed, which involves a lot of screaming and growling. This style can put a considerable strain on the vocal cords if not done with proper technique. Over time, this led to the development of vocal cord issues, including nodules or hemorrhages. \n\nIn addition to the vocal strain from performing, consistent touring and rigorous schedules likely contributed to the wear and tear on his voice. Sykes has openly discussed undergoing surgery to repair his damaged vocal cords and having to go through a period of vocal rest and rehabilitation to recover and adapt his singing style to maintain his vocal health.",
